TITLE: Using Async Ratelimiting in Request Handler with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use async ratelimiting in a request handler. It sets the async option when calling the limit method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unkeyed/unkey/blob/main/apps/www/content/blog/introducing-ratelimiting.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
async function handler(request: NextApiRequest) {
  const identifier = request.getUserId();

  const ratelimit = await unkey.limit(identifier, {
    async: true,
  });
  if (!ratelimit.success) {
    return new Response("try again later", { status: 429 });
  }
  // handle the request here
