TITLE: Implementing HTTPS Server with TLS in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a secure HTTPS server in Node.js using TLS. It loads server key and certificate files, creates an HTTPS server that listens on port 443, and responds with a simple message. This implementation ensures all communications with the API are encrypted using TLS.
